# 3. Normalize the different stains with respect to the training data
<!-- #endregion -->

```python cellView="form" id="hFFN4bior9k3"
# @title Fit a tissue color normalization transform for each different class of tissue
from tiatoolbox.tools import stainnorm

stain_normalizer_tissues = []

for class_id in range(4):
    # Look for the largest image (more content variability)
    all_tissue_ids = np.nonzero(np.array(train_labels) == class_id)[0]

    all_shapes = np.array([skimage.io.imread(train_images_fns[id]).shape[:2] for id in all_tissue_ids])

    target_id = np.argmax(np.prod(all_shapes, axis=1))

    im_train = skimage.io.imread(train_images_fns[target_id])

    stain_normalizer = stainnorm.VahadaneNormalizer()
    stain_normalizer.fit(im_train)

    stain_normalizer_tissues.append(stain_normalizer)
```

```python id="qTyqoG0Hr9k4" cellView="form"
# @title Add the Numpy array to PyTorch tensor transforms to the pipelines
pipeline_tissues = []

for stain_normalizer in stain_normalizer_tissues:
    pipeline = transforms.Compose([
        stain_normalizer.transform,
        transforms.ToTensor(),
        transforms.Resize((342, 342)),
        transforms.CenterCrop((299, 299)),
        transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.485, 0.456, 0.406],
                             std=[0.229, 0.224, 0.225]),
    ])

    pipeline_tissues.append(pipeline)

```

# 4. Extract the features from our dataset with Inception V3
<!-- #endregion -->

<!-- #region id="MdnLKWteoAI0" -->
### Modify the final classifier layer dl_model.fc to return the features extracted from the input image by changing it with a torch.nn.Identity module
<!-- #endregion -->

<!-- #region id="y92l_93Uo76r" -->
 The classifier layer is commonly implemented as a MultiLayer Perceptron (Fully connected) at the end of the models.
The specific name of that layer can vary between implementations.
<!-- #endregion -->

```python colab={"base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"} outputId="07ed76a3-dcb8-45bf-e713-a1c81afe3027" id="JtiTm_k7r9k4"
dl_model.fc
```

```python id="gVI3ClTar9k5"
dl_model.fc = torch.nn.Identity()
```

<!-- #region id="V8noVce8r9k5" -->
 Even if the model is set to evaluation mode, it will still compute the gradients of the whole operations.

To prevent this, wrap the model call inside `with torch.no_grad():`
<!-- #endregion -->

```python colab={"base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"} outputId="bc965f12-9973-470d-de46-bb50e12306ad" id="xs64ZTfOr9k5"
im = skimage.io.imread(train_images_fns[0])

tissue_id = train_labels[0]

x_sample = pipeline_tissues[tissue_id](im)

with torch.no_grad():
    fx = dl_model(x_sample[None, ...])

fx.shape
```

```python colab={"base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"} outputId="1df3b483-9413-435d-ca60-88b7e44a51d8" id="9G5jHLSMr9k5"
fx.requires_grad
```

<!-- #region id="_0-XkU9Or9k6" -->
## Iterate our dataset to generate the feature vector of each image in the training and test sets
<!-- #endregion -->

```python colab={"base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/", "height": 49, "referenced_widgets": ["a465e89bc5d54ac4b43757d5d1dabc49", "8ecc57ef91494a7099a8ae05f1f21b9d", "8ef508501a604cf291bd25cc61805486", "e39d5b20498143f89f1e8c82f20e5a8e", "506d77924c9a41e8858cd1926a822ca4", "dde57d270e6445a99e13540829ba5464", "9ff81c9e9e56471686b3fe735730264f", "8c51e73532764d3e9d4f0560ef226cbb", "a051d7b0e07442aabefc76af95373467", "24d36851eb3e41db8160573e66c03622", "37f2d80327e644c397148b941f14fc0c"]} outputId="9e9c1551-2ac6-44e1-ea06-8930ab5b68f0" id="Qczb9oRIr9k6"
import tqdm.auto as tqdm

X_train = []
y_train = []
for im_fn, lab in tqdm.tqdm(zip(train_images_fns, train_labels), total=len(train_images_fns), position=0):
    im = skimage.io.imread(im_fn)

    x_sample = pipeline_tissues[lab](im)

    with torch.no_grad():
        fx = dl_model(x_sample[None, ...])

    X_train.append(fx[0, ...].numpy())
    y_train.append(lab)

X_train = np.array(X_train)
y_train = np.array(y_train)
```

```python colab={"base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/", "height": 49, "referenced_widgets": ["0a396c205d31457a9a3e078484364ebb", "922b08d34e6d4de8ae7ca8e821fe4185", "2f32f893d2d24f20b3fbffbc013efb7a", "c3c1b0ee843a4d79ad6cef42e12e2abe", "9ecb8ac341684898a320402a3e966b22", "8802b4388b314478b1a70afd3d9c3d92", "05f120620b1248a68ac686ca39f2c9e0", "8ccb5c39196c4710a1c1b63f123389d4", "9f9757dd215b44f9b127f447f9ae2b52", "d98efd929cad4731b5907d6fcf973833", "748afab346f14908b882648f33ade060"]} outputId="3b8d730d-edeb-4da0-84ac-bb35c4dbe0a0" id="e39Y67Jhr9k6"
X_test = []
y_test = []
for im_fn, lab in tqdm.tqdm(zip(test_images_fns, test_labels), total=len(test_images_fns), position=0):
    im = skimage.io.imread(im_fn)

    x_sample = pipeline_tissues[lab](im)

    with torch.no_grad():
        fx = dl_model(x_sample[None, ...])

    X_test.append(fx[0, ...].numpy())
    y_test.append(lab)

X_test = np.array(X_test)
y_test = np.array(y_test)
```

# 6. Measure the per-tissue performance
<!-- #endregion -->

```python id="4T6xJ1J4r9k-"
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay
```

```python colab={"base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/", "height": 510} outputId="bd6e9f47-9a59-4900-f341-805dc3a0d7d1" id="qcX4d8Fqr9k-"
y_train_pred = clf.predict(X_train)
confmat_train = confusion_matrix(y_train, y_train_pred)
confmat_train = confmat_train / confmat_train.sum(axis=1, keepdims=True)

disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confmat_train, display_labels=tissue_classes)
disp.plot(xticks_rotation="vertical", colorbar=False)
```

```python colab={"base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/", "height": 510} outputId="d8a20f46-777f-427c-84d4-642f0a9dfd4c" id="7qUMCFhCr9k-"
y_test_pred = clf.predict(X_test)
confmat_test = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_test_pred)
confmat_test = confmat_test / confmat_test.sum(1, keepdims=True)

disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confmat_test, display_labels=tissue_classes)
disp.plot(xticks_rotation="vertical", colorbar=False)
```
